        public THIS makeImageCaptureOnFinish()
        Marks that it is needed to produce a BufferedImage after invocation of Function.apply(Object) on built resulted Function. This image is produced by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object)

        NOTE 1

        This image is produced if there is any subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor that may produce a BufferedImage.

        NOTE 2

        A subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor should be able to handle resulted values R on success or input values T on failure.
